// The aws CLI surface as exec-dialect policy (cli-guard v0.12.0 execverb).
// One open-passthrough grant keeps the funnel comprehensive - any service or
// operation routes through ward - while the aws-read gate denies read-only
// verbs touching sensitive resources pre-send (secrets / credentials /
// tfstate / backups / admin+root role ARNs, the awsgate default set).
// Engine-verified in cli-guard's execverb tests against this exact shape;
// binary wiring lands with the driver exec transport (cli-guard#131).
wrap ward ops aws {
    exec aws

    can run "*" {
        gate aws-read {
            allow-env "WARD_AWS_ALLOW_SENSITIVE_READ"
        }
        describe "open aws passthrough behind the sensitive-read gate"
    }
}
